    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-25T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-25T05:00:00-05:00" n="773"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/631: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gwynn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-25T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 25, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 25—11:54
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>307. My 296, August 21, 10 a.m., and Department’s 135, August 19, 10 a.m. [<hi
                        rend="smallcaps">p.m</hi>.] I presented at 11 this morning the informal <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> to the Lebanese Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs, Philippe Boulos. He said he hoped to be able to reply soon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gwynn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
